headline: 3 Blue-Chip Dividend Stocks Trading at Multiyear Lows
summary: Buying a dividend stock at a cheap valuation can be a great move for several reasons.  Three stocks that may be underrated options for dividend investors to consider today are PepsiCo (NASDAQ: PEP), United Parcel Service (NYSE: UPS), and Merck (NYSE: MRK).  Shares of beverage and snack giant PepsiCo haven't traded at this price since 2021, and its price-to-earnings (P/E) ratio has only been this low a couple times in the past five years.
